                <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/1877a: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Peru (<persName type="to">Dearing</persName>)</hi>
                    <note n="13" xml:id="d149fn13">The same, on the same date, to the diplomatic
                        representatives in Argentina (No. 47) and in Brazil (No. 52).</note>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-07-26T17:00:00-04:00"
                            >July 26, 1932—5 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>35. Department advised that Minister of Foreign Affairs of Chile yesterday
                    invited Argentine and Brazilian Ambassadors and Peruvian Chargé to exchange
                    ideas with him regarding the Chaco situation and measures to be taken to prevent
                    war.</p>
                <pb facs="0250" n="146" xml:id="pg_146"/>
                <p>Department advised that Brazilian Ambassador in Buenos Aires took this matter up
                    previously with Argentine Minister of Foreign Affairs for joint action between
                    those two Governments and that Argentina replied that it felt that most
                    effective action at present is to support the Neutral Commission in Washington
                    and to urge the two Governments to remain in Washington and to try to arrive at
                    a settlement here.</p>
                <p>The Department and neutral representatives will welcome any recommendations in
                    this sense which may be made by the neighboring countries to the Paraguayan and
                    Bolivian Governments.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
